<!-- journalDescription for publastrsocipaci -->


<div id="journalDesc">
<h3 class="sectionHeader">Journal Description</h3>
<i>Publications of the Astronomical Society of the Pacific</i>, the technical journal of the Astronomical Society of the Pacific (ASP), has been published regularly since 1889, as part of the ASP&#8217;s mission to advance the science of astronomy and disseminate astronomical information. The journal provides an outlet for astronomical results of a scientific nature and serves to keep readers in touch with current astronomical research. It contains refereed research and
<br />
instrumentation papers, invited reviews, and dissertation summaries.
</div>


            
</div>
</div>

